<br>
We have grown as a guild--and will continue to grow because we<br>
have something that other people want: friendship and kindness.<br>
There is not enough of that in Norrath--or any other world!<br>
<br>
Lately we have begun to notice a lot of new faces and names,<br>
and our family doesn't seem as close-knit and &quot;cosy&quot; as it did in the <br>
beginning. It's really good for us to talk about how we feel about<br>
this rather than just run away and stop playing our guild<br>
characters when we feel a little lost or left out. Also, talking<br>
about it gets us all thinking about what we can do to fix it. <br>
<br>
Take heart dear friends--it is nowhere near hopeless. There <br>
are a lot of things we can do. I suggest here and now that <br>
we start trying a few things at a time and seeing how we like them.<br>
<br>
In another message here we talk about Guild Raids and Hunting--<br>
that is something that will help us stay in contact with each other <br>
while hunting. And there are many other things we can do.<br>
<br>
Lets start with some Guild-Only Events. I have a couple of <br>
ideas I want to suggest here and I hope you will add your <br>
ideas here:<br>
<br>
Idea: Surnaming Party! Once or twice a month we could have a <br>
party for those people who have reached level 20 and are entitled to <br>
a surname. Some people might even wait and put their surname on <br>
at the party. Some people might want to come to the party and have <br>
their guildmates help them find the perfect surname--or if they already <br>
know the name they want, we could have a contest to see if anyone <br>
can guess it (with hints provided).  And we could all tell the stories<br>
behind our names. There are other things we<br>
could do with this Surnaming Party too.<br>
<br>
Idea: Fledgling Meet and Greet! Once or twice a month we could have <br>
a party to meet and greet all the people who have joined Random Acts <br>
since the last party. Fledglings would be encouraged to come with stories <br>
about their character, their travels in Norrath, and their most memorable <br>
moments (great idea Jellybean!). Regular members would be able to put a <br>
face to those new names--and a personality too! This would also be a <br>
great place to get drunk!<br>
<br>
Idea: Celebrity Roast! Once a month we could pick a few members of <br>
Random Acts and toast and roast them just like they do at those <br>
celebrity roasts! People would tell their stories about the members and <br>
we'd all have a good laugh. Another good place to get drunk!<br>
<br>
Idea: Guild Swap Meet! Once a month we could all bring whatever we<br>
have been saving in the bank and swap and trade with other guild members.<br>
<br>
Idea: Trade Skills Party! Come and teach a trade to other guild members--<br>
show them where to buy supplies, how to make items and in what order, <br>
how much to sell them for and so on. I remember in the beginning, Tindar <br>
kept telling everyone he was practicing a certain trade skill so if we needed <br>
something we could all go to him for it! As time went by, he kept adding <br>
more and more trade skills. I was wondering if he was going to have time <br>
for anything else there for awhile! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
I myself have practiced many trade skills in the year and a half I've been <br>
playing Everquest including jewelrycraft, blacksmithing, baking, tailoring, <br>
and a mastery of pottery. I don't do trade skills now as much as I used to <br>
but I would be happy to share my knowledge at an event. It would be a<br>
lot easier to share these skills at an event rather than while we<br>
are trying to hunt or raid dungeons, so I think this event would be very useful.<br>
When I was playing an Enchanter I went to an Enchanter Meeting<br>
held on one of the older servers. The Enchanter who called the <br>
meeting spent an hour or more teaching younger <br>
Enchanter about the skill of jewelrycraft, what order to make jewelry in, <br>
and what is fair to charge for your wares. I really appreciated it. Perhaps <br>
after we have done something like this for our members, we could also do <br>
something like this as a Server-wide Guild event.<br>
<br>
Idea: First Aid Camp for Guild-Members only! Lets do for our Fledglings<br>
and Lower-level members what we have been doing for everyone else!<br>
<br>
Okay folkes! There's some grist for the mill! Let's spend this month<br>
concentrating on what we can do for our guildmembers<br>
and ourselves. We already have had many more server-wide events<br>
than most guilds have in a year. Once we feel we all know each other<br>
a lot better, then we can start having server-wide events again.<br>
<br>
Please voice your opinion here of what event we should have first--<br>
and how you would like to see it happen! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Hamadryad<br>
Guild Leader of Random Acts <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Grimmbaldis</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#006400>(8/2/00 10:24:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   first event</span><hr size=1> I like the idea of a swap meet. I've got some stuff that I am sure the lower level members might need.  And now that Dolumar has the taxi service, those of us without gate spells can attend more events.<br>
